wikipedia_page.main: Tonia Williams (born 1966) is a New Zealand-British retired rower. She is the 1993 World Rowing Champion in the lightweight women's four, she won the title with Jane Hall, Alison Brownless and Annamarie Phelps.

response: Hall won the gold medal in the lightweight coxless four with Alison Brownless, Annamarie Dryden and Tonia Williams at the 1993 World Rowing Championships.
